EDITABLE CODE 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
check below for (relatively) easily editable parameters, stimuli, instructions etc. 
Keep in mind that you can use this script as a template and therefore always "mess" with the entire code 
to further customize your experiment.

The parameters you can change are:

/responsetimeout1_signal:		stores the longest response timeouts in ms used in this study for targets
								Note: by default, the longest response timeout in this script is used for blocks
								that test attributes and targets separately (default: 1000ms)
													
(samefor noise trials: by default they are the same in this script)

/isi:							stores the interstimulus interval (time between offset of one stimulus and onset of next)
											


</usermanual>


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE PARAMETERS: change editable parameters here
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

<parameters>
/ responsetimeout1_signal = 600
/ responsetimeout1_noise = 600
/ isi = 250
</parameters>

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE STIMULI: change editable stimuli here
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

<item targetAlabel>
/ 1 = "Me"
</item>

First nameof participant is added during runtime
<item TargetA>
/ 1 = "me"
/ 2 = "myself"
</item>

Note: the Noise for Target A are the items of Target B
<item NoiseA>
/ 1 = "they"
/ 2 = "them"
/ 3 = "those"
</item>

<item targetBlabel>
/ 1 = "Not me"
</item>

<item TargetB>
/ 1 = "they"
/ 2 = "them"
/ 3 = "those"
</item>

Note: the noise for Target B are target A items
<item NoiseB>
/ 1 = "me"
/ 2 = "myself"
</item>


<item attributeAlabel>
/ 1 = "Nice"
</item>

<item attributeA>
/ 1 = "excellent"
/ 2 = "heaven"
/ 3 = "joy"
/ 4 = "trust"
/ 5 = "peace"
/ 6 = "enjoyment"
/ 7 = "friend"
/ 8 = "honest"
/ 9 = "sweetheart"
/ 10 = "love"
/ 11 = "freedom"
/ 12 = "paradise"
</item>

<item attributeBlabel>
/ 1 = "Nasty"
</item>

<item attributeB>
/ 1 = "murder"
/ 2 = "cancer"
/ 3 = "war"
/ 4 = "disaster"
/ 5 = "hatred"
/ 6 = "slaughter"
/ 7 = "bomb"
/ 8 = "agony"
/ 9 = "torture"
/ 10 = "slime"
/ 11 = "filth"
/ 12 = "traitor"
</item>

**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE INSTRUCTIONS: change instructions here
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
<instruct>
/ wait = 1000 
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3.0%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
</instruct>


<surveypage intro1>
/ caption = "
<br><br>
<center><i>Please read the instructions carefully before proceeding with the task.</i></center><br><br>
This research investigates cognitive processes that are used in decisions that involve memory. 
We are seeking to develop and test theories of the cognitive processes that occur outside of awareness in the routine use of memory. 
Stimuli for the category task will be presented on this display screen, 
and your responses will be entered <%expressions.buttoninstruct2%>.<br><br> 
You will have an opportunity to practice before your responses are recorded."
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = white
/ showpagenumbers = false
/ showquestionnumbers = false
</surveypage>

<surveypage intro2>
/ caption = "<br><br>
This task assumes that you can read English fluently, and that your vision is normal or corrected to normal.<br><br>
The tasks that you will be doing in this experiment involve category judgment. 
For instance, in one condition your task may be to search for all the words that represent the categories 'nice' 
(e.g., joy) or the category 'me' (e.g., myself).<br><br>
All categorizations will be made with the space bar <%expressions.buttoninstruct1%>.<br><br> 
When you see a word that belongs to one of the categories (e.g., 'nice' or 'me') hit the space bar <%expressions.buttoninstruct1%> as fast as possible. 
~n~nIgnore words that do not belong to either category."
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = white
/ showpagenumbers = false
/ showquestionnumbers = false
</surveypage>

<surveypage intro3>
/ caption = "<br><br>
The words you will be looking for will be from the 4 groups listed below.<br><br><br>
me (white letters): me, myself<br><br> 
Not me (white letters): they, them, those<br><br>
<font color='turquoise'>Nice (blue letters): excellent, heaven, joy, trust, peace, enjoyment, friend, honest, sweetheart, love, freedom, paradise<br><br>
Nasty (blue letters): murder, cancer, war, disaster, hatred, slaughter, bomb, agony, torture, slime, filth, traitor</font><br><br><br>
The color coding of the words is there to help distinguish between the categories."
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = white
/ showpagenumbers = false
/ showquestionnumbers = false
/ questions = [1 = name]
</surveypage>

<textbox name>
/ caption = "your first name:"
/ required = true
/ maxchars = 50
/txcolor = blue
/ position = (45%, 20%)
/ textboxsize = (30%, 5%)
/ responsefontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
</textbox>


<surveypage intro4>
/ caption = "<br><br>
The task is fast-paced and hard. In fact, you may at times find it very difficult to 
correctly classify ANY of the trials. Do not despair. <br><br>
This task is designed to be difficult and no one is expected to perform it perfectly. 
Please persevere and just try to catch as many words as possible.<br><br>
You will have an opportunity to practice before the task begins.<br><br>
We will start now with a training procedure to get you familiarized with the four categories and stimuli used in this task.
There will be a training block for each of the four categories. The computer will alert you when the categories change.<br><br>
Hit START when you are ready to start the training."
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ txcolor = white
/ showpagenumbers = false
/ showquestionnumbers = false
</surveypage>

<page end>
<center><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>
You have reached the end of the task.
<h1>Thank you!</h1></center>
</page>

<item reminders>
/ 1 = "Let's start the categorization task
~n~nWords will appear in the center of the screen, one by one, at high speed. These words may or may not belong to the category you see printed at the top.
~nPress the space bar as fast as you can if the word belongs to the category you see at the top. If they do not belong to the category, don't do anything. Just wait for the next word.
~nIf you made an error, a red X appears below the word. Otherwise, you will see a green 'O'.
~n~n~nPress the space bar to start practice trials."
/ 2 = "New category - Press the space bar for practice trials"
/ 3 = "The set-up has changed. Instead of only one category, you now see TWO categories printed at the top.
~nPress the space bar as fast as you can if the word appearing in the center belongs to EITHER one of the two categories you see at the top. Don't do anything if the word does not belong to either one of the categories.
~n~n~nPress the space bar for practice trials."
/ 4 = "New categories - Press the space bar for practice trials"
</item>

<text trainingEnd>
/ items = ("The training session has ended.
~n~nPress the space bar to continue.")
/ position = (50%, 65%) 
/ size = (60%, 50%)
/ txcolor = white 
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 2.67%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ vjustify = center
/ hjustify = center
</text>


<text testTrialReminder>
/ items = ("You are now starting the main trials.
~nPress the space bar as fast as you can if the word appearing in the center belongs to EITHER one of the 2 categories you see at the top.
~n~n~nPress the space bar to start.")
/ position = (50%, 65%) 
/ size = (60%, 50%)
/ txcolor = white 
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 2.67%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/ vjustify = center
/ hjustify = center
</text>


<expressions>
/ buttoninstruct1 = if (computer.touch && !computer.hasKeyboard) {"button";} else {"key";}
/ buttoninstruct2 = if (computer.touch && !computer.hasKeyboard) {"using response buttons on your screen"} else {"on the keyboard";}
</expressions>

